org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.transformation.base.utils

Class ModelManagement

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.papyrus.designer.transformation.base.utils.ModelManagement

  • public class ModelManagement
extends Object
    Manages a model (and the associated resource). Allows saving this model. It uses its own static resource set.

      • getPath

        public String getPath(org.eclipse.core.resources.IProject project,
                      String subFolder,
                      String filename)
        Return a path based on project, folder and file name
        Parameters:
        project - an existing project
        subFolder - a subfolder within the project (will be created, if it does not exist) if null, the project will be saved in the root of the project
        filename - the name of the file or null (in his case, the name of the model with the postfix .uml is used)
        Returns:
        The access path to a file

      • createNewModel

        public static ModelManagement createNewModel(String name)
                                      throws TransformationException
        Create a new empty model from an existing model that applies the same profiles and has the same imports
        Parameters:
        existingModel - an existing model
        name - the name of the new model
        copyImports - true, if (top-level) package import should be copied from the existing into the new model
        Returns:
        the model-management instance for the new model (use getModel() to obtain the actual model)
        Throws:
